$interpreted: Jia-Shen: Whew... good thing we didn't really start fightin' back there.
Jia-Shen: I knew relations between kingdoms were stressed, but I didn't realize they were THIS bad. Bein' a diplomat's tough work...
Sennosuke: If it's so tough, then why don't you quit?
Jia-Shen: You again!?
Sennosuke: Don't be scared, I'm just here to attend your farewell dinner.
Jia-Shen: Farewell dinner? When did I say I was leavin'?
Sennosuke: Doesn't matter what you say, really. It matters what I say.
Sennosuke: I do remember warning you to be careful.
Sennosuke: Come on, let's teach turtle-boy how we do things in the east!
Sennosuke: Not bad! Too bad for you there's plenty more where that came from.
Sennosuke: What are you waiting for? Get him!
Jia-Shen: Agh!
Kid: B-Boss!
Sennosuke: What!? Can't you see I'm busy!?
Kid: I'm v-v-very sorry, b-but the... the arbiter's summoning you to the hall!
Sennosuke: The arbiter...
Sennosuke: Hmph... I'll have to be going, then.
Sennosuke: But you all make sure to take real good care of our guest while I'm gone.
Jia-Shen: (Ugh... there's too many of 'em!)
Jerk Kid: He's finally down! Get him! Hit him! Knock him out!
Mean Kid: We're gonna make the biggest bowl of turtle soup you've ever seen!
Jia-Shen: I'm not... a turtle... I'm...
Mean Kid: Maple leaves? Why are they red...?
Mean Kid: Ah!!
Jerk Kid: Huh?
Jerk Kid: What the... there's gotta be someone watchin' out for him. I don't like this... let's get outta here!
Jia-Shen: You're...
Maeok: Well, since everyone is here, we should get started.
Maeok: Himawari, are you still not willing to speak?
Himawari: ......
Maeok: Then I'll ask you first, Sennosuke.
Sennosuke: Ask away~
Maeok: Some days ago, your confidant, Otoshi, was found trying to assassinate Miranda. How do you explain yourself?
Sennosuke: Otoshi? I haven't spoken to him in ages.
Maeok: So you mean it was not you who gave Otoshi those orders?
Sennosuke: Arbiter, I've got nothing to do with Himawari, why would I get involved in her dirty work?
Maeok: ...Fine.
Maeok: Looks like I'll have to turn to you, now, Miranda. I expect answers.
Miranda: ...When I was younger, I met a young girl in the Kingdom of the Sun. She was fleeing home, plagued by constant pain...
Miranda: She was a leopard, and her name... was Himawari.
Shun: So you're saying you know the real Himawari?
Shun: Where is she, then?
Miranda: The Himawari I knew... died many years ago in the Kingdom of the Sun from her illnesses.
Shun: But...
Miranda: She never told me anything about her past... I could tell she was haunted by horrible memories... terrible secrets...
Miranda: Right before she died, she told me why she was always in pain. It was because of her power... a power she transferred to me.
Bull Chieftain: Himawari transferred her power to you!? That's... unforgivable! A heavy crime!!
Toyokuni: Settle down... Let her finish.
Miranda: Himawari never wanted it... she hated her power. I told her I wanted to join the tournament, I wanted to show her that her power had merit.
Miranda: But then suddenly, the night before the tournament, after I'd gotten the holy talisman and traveled east...
Miranda: This girl came out of nowhere. A leopard taken in by the Qilin Tribe. She held the holy talisman and could make the Leopard's Eye glow.
Soohyeon: ...And that's the Himawari we know, right?
Miranda: The fact that she can make the Leopard's Eye glow means she has the real power of a leopard.
Miranda: ...So I... I'm so confused... I don't know what's real anymore.
Law: I think I can add something of use to this discussion, if you would allow me to speak.
Law: Miranda told me everything, and asked for my help.
Maeok: ...So, back when we couldn't find you, you were...
Law: That's right. Miranda was to attend the tournament, so she couldn't leave...
Law: I traveled in her stead, looking for any information I could find on the Leopard Tribe, and their untimely decline.
Miranda: And while I was waiting for Master Law's return, I happened to witness Sennosuke... expose this Himawari as a human!
Miranda: And that means... that means the Himawari I knew must be the real one!
Qing-Feng: The Leopard Tribe's power grows when it is transferred to a new host.
Qing-Feng: Our ancestors feared this would turn the Leopard Tribe into a threat, and so deemed that transfer of power a serious crime.
Qing-Feng: And so I do not understand, Arbiter Maeok, why you have not already locked these two up and thrown away the key?
Maeok: Please, Qing-Feng, try to be calm. Himawari is still a tournament contestant, so she cannot currently be convicted of any crime.
Qing-Feng: So then arrest the other one! She's already lost, has she not!?
Law: Nothing is certain yet! Why must you continue to meddle!?
Qing-Feng: And this Master Law was withholding information, as well! You should lock him up just the same!
Law: Hmph. I'd wager Qing-Feng here is being manipulated by his own niece. No wonder he wants to end this as quickly as possible!
Qing-Feng: Look who's talking, Law! You know what they say about people who make assumptions!
Maeok: Please, you two...
Sennosuke: Listen, I've heard enough to know this has got nothing to do with me, so I'll be going now. Good luck, everyone.
Law: And where do you think you're going?
Law: Contestants can't be arrested until the tournament is over, but conspirators can be!
Panther Chieftain: ...Law? Are you suggesting that Sennosuke had something to do with Himawari transferring her power?
Bull Chieftain: What!? That's ridiculous!
Law: Indeed, I am. And I have proof.
Soohyeon: A leopard!
